The 'ATP World Tour 250 series' is the newest series for tennis tournaments of
the Association of Tennis Professionals (ATP) from the 2009 ATP World Tour. It
is the lowest tier of events on the tour, and is a continuation of the ATP
International Series.

The series includes 40 tournaments, with a number of 250 rankings points to win
for the events' singles champions â€“which accounts for the name of the
series. Draws are either consisted of 28, 32, 48, or 56 for singles and 16 and
24 for doubles.
